Presidential aspirant, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, is currently in Ogun State to meet Governor Dapo Abiodun, including leaders of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the State. Tinubu was led into the Presidential Lodge, Ibara, Abeokuta by Gov Abiodun at 4:35pm. It is said the former Lagos Governor is in Ogun to meet with APC delegates ahead of the APC presidential primary election.